\pard\plain \intbl\itap1\qj{\f0\fs24\b1\scaps\cb5\highlight5 Deeper Study}{\f0\fs24\b1\cb5\highlight5  # 1}
\par\plain \intbl\itap1{\f0\fs24\cb5\highlight5 (48:17\endash 18) }{\f0\fs24\b1\cb5\highlight5 Blessings\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 Birthright\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 Firstborn\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 Sovereignty, Of God\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 Grace}{\f0\fs24\cb5\highlight5 : in Jacob\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s day, the firstborn was always to receive the best\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 a double portion\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 of the family\u8217\'92s inheritance and blessing. But often, in God\u8217\'92s sovereignty, the younger son was chosen to be more greatly used in God\u8217\'92s purposes. This is one of the facts immediately noticed throughout Scripture.}
\par\pard\plain \intbl\itap1\tx1080\li1080\fi-360\sb180\qj{\f0\fs24\cb5\highlight5 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8658\'3F\tab Seth was chosen before Cain.}
\par\pard\plain \intbl\itap1\tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj{\f0\fs24\cb5\highlight5 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8658\'3F\tab Shem was chosen before Japheth.}
\par\pard\plain \intbl\itap1\tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj{\f0\fs24\cb5\highlight5 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8658\'3F\tab Abraham was chosen before Haran.}
\par\pard\plain \intbl\itap1\tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj{\f0\fs24\cb5\highlight5 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8658\'3F\tab Isaac was chosen before Ishmael.}
\par\pard\plain \intbl\itap1\tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj{\f0\fs24\cb5\highlight5 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8658\'3F\tab Jacob was chosen before Esau.}
\par\pard\plain \intbl\itap1\tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj{\f0\fs24\cb5\highlight5 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8658\'3F\tab Ephraim was chosen before Manasseh.}
\par\pard\plain \intbl\itap1\tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj{\f0\fs24\cb5\highlight5 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8658\'3F\tab Moses was chosen before his brother.}
\par\pard\plain \intbl\itap1\tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj{\f0\fs24\cb5\highlight5 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8658\'3F\tab Gideon was chosen before his brothers.}
\par\pard\plain \intbl\itap1\tx1080\li1080\fi-360\qj{\f0\fs24\cb5\highlight5 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8658\'3F\tab David was chosen before his brothers.}
\par\pard\plain \intbl\itap1\sb180\qj{\f0\fs24\cb5\highlight5 In each of these cases, God was demonstrating two great truths: His sovereignty and His grace.}
\par\pard\plain \intbl\itap1\fi360\qj{\f0\fs24\cb5\highlight5 1. There was God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s sovereignty. Man has tended toward choosing the older child to take on the responsibility for the family when needed, not always, but usually. But God knows the human heart, and He has the right as God to choose any person He wants. Therefore, when He chose the younger son, God\u8217\'92s sovereignty was honored and man\u8217\'92s evaluation and plans were humbled.}
\par\plain \intbl\itap1{\f0\fs24\cb5\highlight5 2. There was God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s grace. God\u8217\'92s grace is always seen when He chooses the younger son. If the laws and customs of men were followed, the younger son would never receive the greater blessings. If he ever received them, it was because man\u8217\'92s law and custom were bypassed. Therefore, when the younger son received the greater blessing, it was being freely given to him. The blessing was given by grace, entirely undeserved, unmerited, and unearned by law. The younger son received the greater blessing simply because God freely chose him to receive them.}
\par\plain \intbl\itap1{\f0\fs24\cb5\highlight5 This meant that he owed all the blessings to God. All that he had belonged and was due to God, not to himself nor to any other person. (See note, pt. 2\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 Ge. 25:23; also see notes\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 Ro. 9:7\endash 13 for more discussion.)}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0  Leadership Ministries Worldwide. (1996). }{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosres/posbkjv01ge2?ref=Bible.Ge48.8-22&off=8473&ctx=ildren%E2%80%9D+(Tit.+2:4).%0a~Deeper+Study+%23+1%0a(48"}{\fldrslt\f2\fs24\b0\i1\ul\ulc0\cf3 Genesis (Chapters 12\endash 50)}}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0  (Vol. II, p. 387). Chattanooga, TN: Leadership Ministries Worldwide.}
